hands_on_practices.solution:
We treat the term in $H_I$ which scatters two condensate particles ($\mathbf k=\mathbf p=0$) into $(\mathbf q,-\mathbf q)$ as a perturbation 
$$H'=\frac{g}{2A}\sum_{\mathbf q\neq0}\Bigl(a^\dagger_{\mathbf q}a^\dagger_{-\mathbf q}a_0a_0+\text{h.c.}\Bigr)\,. $$

1. The second‐order correction to the ground‐state energy is
$$
\Delta E^{(2)}
=-\sum_{\mathbf q\neq0}\frac{\bigl|\langle1_{\mathbf q},1_{-\mathbf q}|H'|0\rangle\bigr|^2}
{E_{1_{\mathbf q},1_{-\mathbf q}}-E_0}
\,. $$

2. The matrix element for exciting two condensate bosons is
$$
M_{\mathbf q}
=\frac{g}{2A}\langle1_{\mathbf q},1_{-\mathbf q}|\,a^\dagger_{\mathbf q}a^\dagger_{-\mathbf q}a_0a_0\,|0\rangle
=\frac{g}{2A}\sqrt{N_0(N_0-1)}
\approx\frac{g\,n_0}{2}\,. 
$$

3. The energy denominator is 
$$
E_{1_{\mathbf q},1_{-\mathbf q}}-E_0
=2\epsilon_{\mathbf q}
=2\frac{\hbar^2q^2}{2m}
=\frac{\hbar^2q^2}{m}\,.
$$

4. Thus
$$
\Delta E^{(2)}
=-\sum_{\mathbf q\neq0}\frac{(g\,n_0/2)^2}{2\epsilon_{\mathbf q}}
=-\frac{g^2n_0^2}{4}\sum_{\mathbf q\neq0}\frac1{2\epsilon_{\mathbf q}}
=-\frac{g^2n_0^2}{8}\sum_{\mathbf q\neq0}\frac1{\epsilon_{\mathbf q}}\,.
$$

5. Converting the sum to an integral in two dimensions with cutoffs $q_0\le q\le\Lambda$,
$$
\sum_{\mathbf q\neq0}\frac1{\epsilon_{\mathbf q}}
\approx A\int\frac{d^2q}{(2\pi)^2}\,\frac1{\frac{\hbar^2q^2}{2m}}
=A\frac{2m}{\hbar^2}\int\frac{d^2q}{(2\pi)^2}\frac1{q^2}
=\frac{2m\,A}{\hbar^2}\frac1{2\pi}\int_{q_0}^{\Lambda}\frac{dq}{q}
=\frac{m\,A}{\pi\hbar^2}\ln\frac{\Lambda}{q_0}\,. 
$$

6. Therefore the second‐order correction per unit area is
$$
\frac{\Delta E^{(2)}}{A}
=-\frac{g^2n_0^2}{8}\,\frac{m}{\pi\hbar^2}\ln\frac{\Lambda}{q_0}
=-\frac{m\,g^2\,n_0^2}{8\pi\hbar^2}\,\ln\frac{\Lambda}{q_0}\,. 
$$

Since at $T=0$ the grand potential equals the energy, we have
$$
\frac{\Delta\Omega^{(2)}}{A}
=-\frac{m\,g^2\,n_0^2}{8\pi\hbar^2}\ln\!\bigl(\tfrac{\Lambda}{q_0}\bigr)\,. 
$$
